{
  "stem": "19921.1",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 21.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "As for what was going on in Germany, I knew also 1938, because one of my uncles married a girl, which-- from across the border.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "The town of Bytom, which she was a-- she was born German.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Her parents were Polish, Polish Jews.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But she was born in Germany, and as far as she was concerned, she was German.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "She didn't even speak any Polish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And in 1938, when the Crystal Night-- just before the Crystal Night, actually, they evac-- they threw all the Polish Jews out.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "No matter if you're born there or not.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "If your grandparents were not German, real German Jews, you could not stay in Germany.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "So they throw all this.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "They did not accept you as a German citizen.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "They threw all those people out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "They virtually throw them out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "They brought them to the borders with the dogs and everything.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And-- the town by the name I remember still.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "It was Bytom.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And that's where my aunt went up.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And that's how I knew what was happening to the German Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "As far as in Poland, there was no-- at that time, there was not-- except the scribbling on the-- on the windows, we didn't know anything what was going on.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "We found that in 1938 that they threw the Jews out.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And as a matter of fact, which will come up later, that's how I met the first time my wife when she was a child.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And she was carried in on a stretcher, because she developed the pneumonia.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "She was a very delicate child then, and she developed pneumonia, so she was so weak that they had to bring her on a stretcher.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And that's where I found out the troubles in Germany.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
